headline.print_headline: As Giant U.S. IPO Nears, Alibaba's China e-Commerce Crown Slips
headline.main: As Giant U.S. IPO Nears, Alibaba's China e-Commerce Crown Slips

lead_paragraph: Alibaba's dominance of online retail in China faces its biggest-ever challenge as the firm founded by Jack Ma in a one-room apartment 15 years ago lines up a U.S. initial public offering that could value the firm at around $140 billion.
